HEADWORD: Biorgan
<hw>Bi*or"gan</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>bi`os</grk> life + E. <ets>organ</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>A physiological organ; a living organ; an organ endowed with
function; -- distinguished from <contr>idorgan</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

